= Sequel Model Validated
Replaces the current "in-build" model validations...

=== Handle Exceptions:
  class SomeModel < Sequel::Model
    is :validated

    attribute_reader :ident
    validates_presence_of :ident

  end

  SomeModel.new.save # raises an ValidationError

  class AnotherModel < Sequel::Model
    is :validated, :without_exception => true

    attribute_reader :ident
    validates_presence_of :ident

  end

  AnotherModel.new.save # does not
  SomeModel.new.save_without_validation # does not even validate

=== Conditional Validations:
  class DontWanna < Sequel::Model(:dont_wannas)
    is :validated

    validates_length_of :name, :on => :update

    def validate_on_create
      errors.add(:foo) = :bar if rand(10) > 5
    end

    validates_format_of :monitor, :with => /16:10/,
      :unless => proc {|r| r.eyes.kind_of? Square}
  end

